  "text": "The UPR and DNA damage responses are simultaneously activated in cells suffering from genomic stress. It has been shown that ER stress enhances proteasomal degradation of Rad51, a key protein involved in the homologous recombination pathway, and which was associated with decreased DNA repair and cell death in irradiated cells [CITATION_1] . In line with such reasoning, it has been more recently reported that ER stress is dominant following DNA damage in cultured tumor cell lines, causing an increase in p53-mediated, genotoxic-induced apoptosis [CITATION_2] .",
